reviews.text: It's a neighborhood mall vibe where mostly only locals would do their shopping here. Typical Aeon mall with clothes, toys, household items etc. Aeon is more popular for their supermarket where you can buy food stuff and groceries. It has a good food court with a variety of affordable Japanese cuisine too.
Nice variety of food. Price could be more reasonable thougu
very good shop, Japanese products,  a great place to hang out, but it can get crowded on weekends

Aeon Style supermarket offers special sales on every Wednesday.  You can join the member to get extra discount on selected items exclusive for member, and 5 percent off on second and twentieth of each month ( the Thankful Day).  Remember to download its apps and you can do express payment without waiting for a long queue to pay, especially in those special sales days where it will be crowded.  The supermarket provides a large variety of goods from Japan, and most of the goods are cheaper than those in APITA.  Free delivery of goods is offered if purchase over HK$500 for member and HK$600 for non member.  Free parking is available for purchase over the specified amount of money.

Updated renovation clean and fresh environment a
nice place for shopping and eating
